{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75c76907-5799-4090-a919-38913be3739d","content":"Here's my proposed architecture and plan:\n\n---\n\n## RAG Q&A Feature — Architecture Plan\n\n### Overview\nAdd two capabilities to the existing minimal Web API:\n1. **Ingestion pipeline** — reads markdown files from `Docs/`, splits them into chunks, generates embeddings, and stores them in a vector store.\n2. **Query endpoint** — accepts a natural-language question, retrieves relevant chunks via similarity search, and sends them as context to an LLM to produce a grounded answer.\n\n---\n\n### High-Level Data Flow\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐      ┌────────────┐      ┌──────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │─────▶│  Chunker   │─────▶│ Vector Store │\n└─────────────┘      └────────────┘      └──────┬───────┘\n                                                 │ similarity search\n┌─────────────┐      ┌────────────┐             │\n│  User Query │─────▶│  Embedder  │─────────────┘\n└─────────────┘      └────────────┘             │\n                                                ▼\n                                        ┌──────────────┐\n                                        │   LLM (GPT)  │──▶ Answer\n                                        └──────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Suggested Tech |\n|-------|---------------|----------------|\n| **Chunking** | Split markdown by heading / fixed token window with overlap | Custom service using Markdig for heading detection |\n| **Embeddings** | Convert chunks → vectors | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` + OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` |\n| **Vector Store** | Persist & query embeddings | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` with in-memory store (swap for Qdrant/Azure AI Search later) |\n| **Retrieval** | Top-K cosine similarity lookup | VectorStore search API |\n| **Generation** | Prompt LLM with retrieved context | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` chat client (OpenAI / Azure OpenAI) |\n| **API Surface** | Expose endpoints | ASP.NET Minimal APIs |\n\n---\n\n### Proposed Endpoints\n\n| Method | Route | Purpose |\n|--------|-------|---------|\n| `POST` | `/ingest` | Trigger re-ingestion of all docs (idempotent) |\n| `POST` | `/ask` | `{ \"question\": \"...\" }` → `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }` |\n\n---\n\n### Chunking Strategy\n- Parse each markdown file with **Markdig**.\n- Split on `##` headings to produce semantically meaningful sections.\n- If a section exceeds a token budget (e.g., 512 tokens), apply a sliding-window split with ~50-token overlap.\n- Each chunk carries metadata: `fileName`, `heading`, `chunkIndex`.\n\n---\n\n### Project Structure (proposed additions)\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentChunker.cs\n│   ├── IngestionService.cs\n│   └── QueryService.cs\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs\n│   └── AskRequest/AskResponse.cs\n├── Endpoints/\n│   ├── IngestEndpoint.cs\n│   └── AskEndpoint.cs\n└── Program.cs  (register services & endpoints)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Configuration (appsettings)\n- `OpenAI:ApiKey` / `OpenAI:EmbeddingModel` / `OpenAI:ChatModel`\n- `Rag:ChunkSize` / `Rag:ChunkOverlap` / `Rag:TopK`\n\n---\n\n### Considerations\n- **Swappable vector store** — code against `IVectorStore` abstraction so you can move from in-memory to a persistent store without changing business logic.\n- **Startup ingestion** — optionally run ingestion on app start via `IHostedService` so the store is warm immediately.\n- **Source citation** — return chunk metadata alongside the answer so users can verify provenance.\n- **Streaming** — the `/ask` endpoint could support `text/event-stream` for token-by-token delivery later.\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"372dbca4-bac0-454c-ad19-9e17984ccd43","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a clear picture of the existing project. It's a minimal .NET 10 Web API with a `Docs/` folder containing markdown files. Let me create a plan for adding a RAG-based Q&A 